The paper deals with natural language processing and knowledge graphs, which are common topics in the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the use of graph-based techniques for knowledge representation, which is relevant to the sub-category of databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper addresses the problem of entity classification, which is a task commonly studied in the sub-category of information retrieval (cs.IR).
